def: A gate keeper; a gate tender.
To soak water; to fill the interstices of with water.
Being on the extreme external part; farthest outward; as, theoutermost row. Boyle.
The act of making acetous or sour; the process of converting,or of becoming converted, into vinegar.
One who fogs; a pettifogger. [Obs.]A beggarly fogger. Terence in English(1614)
To plunge down into; to sink; to immerse. [Obs.]The water in which it was demerged. Boyle.
